
[1]colophony

   COLOPHONY, n. In pharmacy, black resin or turpentine boiled in water
   and dried; or the residuum, after distillation of the etherial oil of
   turpentine, being further urged by a more intense and long continued
   fire. It is so named from Colophon in Ionia, whence the best was
   formerly brought.
